The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Thursday, January 01, 2004 				 Coldest day of season 
 OUR BUREAU 																								Calcutta, Dec. 31: Calcuttans shivered on New Years eve as the Met office recorded the coldest day of the season so far. The weather office recorded a minimum temperature of 12.4 degrees Celsius, two degrees below normal. Dum Dum recorded a minimum temperature of 11.8 degrees. 																								The director of the weather section of the regional meteorological centre at Alipore, K.K. Chakraborty, said the minimum temperature is expected to hover around 12 degrees during the next couple of days.																								The sky is clear and there is no low pressure formation over the Bay of Bengal. This is what we call ideal winter conditions, said Chakraborty.																								Last year, the minimum temperature on New Years eve was 12.2 degrees, slightly lower than this year. 
